==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quadrillion
<hw>Quad*ril"lion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>quater</ets> four times, akin to <ets>quattuor</ets> four, E.
<ets>four</ets>; -- formed like <ets>million</ets>. See <er>Four</er>,
<er>Million</er>.]</ety> <def>According to the French notation, which is
followed also upon the Continent and in the United States, a unit with
fifteen ciphers annexed; according to the English notation, the number
produced by involving a million to the fourth power, or the number
represented by a unit with twenty-four ciphers annexed. See the Note
under <er>Numeration</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

